biography:
Since 2013, Amotus has been providing engineering services, specializing in electronic and software development for custom interconnected solutions. As experts in the Internet of Things (IoT) and innovative solutions, we focus on the remote control and management of connected assets.

To support this, Amotus developed Fundamentum, a fully customizable Platform-as-a-Service (PaaS) designed to manage connected devices. Its scalability and adaptability enable businesses to harness the power of IoT to meet specific project requirements.

With a proven track record of successfully completing hundreds of projects across 15 countries, Amotus has earned the trust of world-renowned companies for its expertise in developing simple, efficient, and certified connected solutions.

Amotus also provides strategic guidance for digital transformation.

Design Services:
Electronics
Firmware
Linux Yocto
Wireless Connectivity
IoT Back-End
Front-End (Mobile, Web, PC)
Amotus a ainsi conçu Fundamentum, une plateforme en tant que service entièrement personnalisable, pour gérer les appareils connectés. Son évolutivité et son adaptabilité permettent de tirer parti de la puissance de l’IdO pour répondre aux exigences de projets spécifiques.

Amotus a réalisé avec succès des centaines de projets dans 15 pays, gagnant la confiance d’entreprises de renommée mondiale pour ses compétences précises dans le développement de solutions connectées simples, efficaces et certifiées.

Amotus offre aussi de l'accompagnement stratégique pour la transformation numérique.

Services de conception :
- Électronique
- Micrologiciel (firmware)

biography:
Issu du secteur des médias et des communications, Raymond Poirier agit à titre de conseiller en communications et valorisation de la recherche à l’Institut intelligence et données (IID) de l'Université Laval depuis décembre 2019.

Après une formation à l’Université Laval, Raymond a été actif tant dans la sphère médiatique de Québec – journaux, télévision et radio, autant qu’au sein du milieu culturel ou communautaire, contractuel ou pigiste pour des actions de communications, rédaction ou animation, ainsi qu’à titre de directeur de production ou de gestionnaire d’événements. Après avoir mené quelques mandats à titre de contractuel pour le compte de l’Institut Technologies de l’information et Sociétés (ITIS) de l’Université Laval, il y a fait le saut à temps plein en 2011, moment à partir duquel il s’est consacré activement à la mise en valeur de la recherche liée au numérique ainsi qu’à son transfert. Après quelques années, il fût également recruté par le CEFRIO, où il agit à titre de chef des communications et porte-parole en 2018-2019, avant de revenir à l'Université Laval et prendre ses fonctions à l'IID.

biography:
I am a Full Professor at Paris-Saclay University, Director of the International Laboratory on Learning Systems (ILLS) and affiliate with the National Centre for Scientific Research (CNRS). I am also a Associate Academic Member at Mila - Quebec AI Institute and Associate Professor at ETS Montreal.  

My research lies at the intersection of security, privacy, and machine learning, and the broader applications to various domains such as healthcare, security and automation. I am especially interested in collaborative agents—AI systems designed to interact, negotiate, and cooperate with both humans and other machines to achieve shared goals. My work aims to develop rigorous, information-theoretic techniques for building safe, trustworthy, and robust multi-agent AI systems, thereby fostering confidence in their behavior and enabling their reliable deployment in societal contexts. 

Previously, my research had a broader interest in Information Theory—the mathematical framework for understanding and quantifying information and its applications to numerous areas of applied mathematics and science such as fundamental limits of distributed compression, statistical decision theory, universal source coding, cooperation, feedback, index coding, and security of communication channels. 

I served as Program General Chair of the  2019 IEEE International Symposium on Information Theory (ISIT), and Area Chair and Senior Area Chair in several conferences such AAAI, ISIT, ITW, CCS, USENIX, NeurIPS, among others, and as  Associate Editor for the IEEE Trans. on Information Forensics and Security.  

I earned my Ph.D. in Physics from Université Paris-Sud (France) in 2007. Upon graduating, I joined the Department of Telecommunications at Supélec and in 2015 the Laboratoire des Signaux et Systèmes (L2S) within Paris-Saclay University.  From 2018 to 2019, I was visiting professor at University of Montreal (Canada) and ÉTS Montreal and from 2019 to 2020, I was visiting researcher at Laboratoire de Mathématiques d’Orsay (France). Previusly, I was visiting professor at University of Chile (Chile), University of Buenos Aires (Argentina), TU Wien - Technische Universität Wien (Austria), Technion (Israel), EPFL - École Polytechnique Fédérale de Lausanne (Switzerland).

biography:
Ingénieure de formation, je suis passionnée de technologie et d’innovation. Œuvrant dans ce domaine depuis 2001, Je travaille à TELUS depuis plus 16 ans. J’ai accompagné des grandes entreprises québécoises  dans leur choix technologiques et dans l’atteinte de leurs objectifs en tirant profit de solutions de télécommunications avant-gardistes avant d’couper le rôle de  Directrice Générale Stratégie et  Développement des affaires. Je me concentre principalement sur la conception d’approches stratégiques et novatrices qui favorisent la croissance dans le segment des grandes entreprises et des organismes publics et parapublics du Québec
Ayant à cœur le rayonnement des femmes en TI et croyant fortement à la sensibilisation de nos jeunes, j’ai participé à la web série sur les femmes en STEM,  Les Catalys. Cette émission a pour objectif  de stimuler l’intérêt des jeunes femmes envers les sciences et les encourager à envisager de faire leurs études et de travailler dans le domaine des STIM (Sciences, Technologies, Ingénierie et Mathématiques). J’ai été également conférencière lors de plusieurs évènements ayant pour but de promouvoir la relève des Femmes en Tech dont la 6ème édition de Femmes en TI, présentée par Le Réseau Action TI. Il y a quelques mois, j’ai joint la Fondation de Centre des Sciences de Montreal à titre de Vice-Présidente et fière représentante de TELUS avec le grand désir de faire une différence  dans la vie de nos jeunes.

--

"Passionate about technology and innovation, I have a bachelor’s degree in Electrical Engineering with a focus on Telecommunications I’ve been working in Tech since 2001. I joined TELUS in 2005 and supported large Quebec companies with their technological roadmap and with achieving their objectives by taking advantage of IT solutions based on leading edge technology. 
As a General Director of Strategy and Business Development, I mainly focus on the design of strategic and innovative approaches that drive growth of large organizations in Quebec Enterprise and Public segment.    
Having the promotion of women in Tech at heart and strongly believing in raising awareness among our young people, I participated in the web series on women in STEM, Les Catalys. The objective of this program is to stimulate interest in science among young women and encourage them to consider studying and working in STEM. I was also a speaker at several events promoting Women in Tech, including the 6th Edition of Femmes en TI, presented by Le Réseau Action TI. I recently joined the Montreal Science Center Foundation as a Vice-President with the hoping to make a difference in the lives of our young people
"

biography:
Luc Tremblay : Stratège | Innovateur | Facilitateur

Fort d'une carrière distinguée de quarante ans, Luc Tremblay s'est imposé comme une force redoutable dans la croissance stratégique des affaires et l'innovation. Son parcours au sein des leaders technologiques mondiaux et ses entreprises entrepreneuriales ont forgé une expertise unique et multifacette, parfaitement adaptée pour guider les organisations à travers des transformations complexes et des expansions de marché. Luc maîtrise le processus de mise sur le marché, de la conception à l'exécution, livrant constamment des revenus accrus et une part de marché étendue.

Une carrière forgée dans la croissance et l'innovation

La vaste expérience de Luc témoigne de son adaptabilité et de son esprit avant-gardiste. Il a occupé des rôles pivots dans un large éventail de fonctions commerciales, notamment la Stratégie, la Gestion, les Opérations, les Ventes, le Développement des affaires et le Marketing. Cette compréhension holistique du paysage commercial lui permet de concevoir et de mettre en œuvre des stratégies qui sont non seulement visionnaires mais aussi opérationnellement solides.

Sa carrière est marquée par un thème constant : la conduite du « nouveau ». Chez /N SPRO, en tant que VP Marketing et Développement des affaires, il a été l'architecte du lancement de nouvelles offres de produits et de l'établissement d'une présence dans de nouvelles zones géographiques. Au cours de son mandat chez Nakisa, il a joué un rôle déterminant dans le lancement de leur Programme de partenariat mondial et a mené avec succès l'entrée de l'entreprise sur le marché latino-américain.

Peut-être l'une des expériences les plus révélatrices a été son passage chez SAP, où il a été un membre fondateur de l'équipe qui a lancé les plateformes révolutionnaires SAP NetWeaver et SAP xApps. Ce rôle exigeait non seulement une compréhension technique approfondie, mais aussi le sens stratégique pour éduquer le marché, bâtir un pipeline de ventes à partir de zéro et établir un modèle de revenus durable pour des solutions entièrement nouvelles.

Méthodologies éprouvées pour un succès prévisible

Luc ne se fie pas uniquement à son intuition. Il est un praticien certifié de cadres de stratégie commerciale de renommée mondiale, y compris la Stratégie Océan Bleu et les méthodologies Strategyzer pour la construction d'entreprises invincibles et le test d'idées commerciales. Cet engagement envers des approches éprouvées et axées sur les données garantit que ses conseils sont ancrés dans les meilleures pratiques qui atténuent les risques et maximisent les chances de succès. Sa récente certification en « Building Invincible Companies » de Strategyzer en mai 2024 souligne son dévouement à l'apprentissage continu et à rester à la pointe de l'innovation stratégique.

Leadership et perspective globale

Les capacités de leadership de Luc s'étendent au-delà des rôles d'entreprise. Ses 12 années de service au conseil d'administration de Desjardins, y compris un mandat en tant que Président, démontrent sa compétence en matière de gouvernance, de surveillance stratégique et de leadership éthique au sein d'une coopérative financière majeure.

De plus, son expérience en tant que Chef de l'exploitation mondial pour le Groupe AUTHENTIC et son travail dans l'établissement d'opérations nord-américaines pour une entreprise basée au Brésil lui ont fourni des informations inestimables sur les nuances culturelles des affaires internationales, en particulier entre l'Amérique du Nord, l'Amérique latine et l'Europe.

Le partenaire idéal pour votre mandat

Aujourd'hui, en tant que PDG de Tremblay Stratégie Innovation, Luc consacre son temps à aider les entreprises en tant que consultant, coach et facilitateur. Il apporte une combinaison rare d'expérience pratique, de prévoyance stratégique et d'une boîte à outils de méthodologies éprouvées.

Pour toute organisation cherchant à naviguer dans les complexités d'un nouveau marché, à lancer un nouveau produit ou à transformer fondamentalement sa direction stratégique, Luc Tremblay n'offre pas seulement des conseils, mais un partenariat. Ses 40 ans de succès sont l'assurance ultime qu'il possède l'expertise, le savoir-faire et les connaissances nécessaires pour faciliter votre mandat et propulser votre organisation vers un avenir plus rentable et innovant.

biography:
Over the past decade, I’ve worked alongside the world’s leading associations and exhibition organizers and large scale conferences to help future-proof their event strategies, supporting more than a thousand events across North America, Europe, and beyond 🌎

When I joined Swapcard, we were a small team with a bold vision for redefining event engagement. Today, we’re a global team of 200+ event experts powering the industry’s leading AI-driven platform, trusted by brands like PCMA, NAVC, Informa, and Koelnmesse to increase engagement, improve exhibitor ROI, and unlock new revenue streams.

As I lead our strategic growth in North America, I partner directly with executive teams to help them modernize their tech stack, streamline operations, and activate year-round communities. My focus is not just on delivering technology, but on enabling measurable outcomes and long-term impact.

I believe the most successful events today are built on three pillars: the right technology, a skilled team to implement it, and the strategic use of data. When these align, events become more than moments, they become engines of industry influence and a lasting heartbeat of the economy.

I have been working in the IT and Telecommunication industry for over 30 years, holding key positions in product development, advanced technology and consulting services. My work experience spanned diverse roles including project manager, system architect, business analyst, researcher and software developer.

Over the last few years, my focus has been on Solana Networks, a company I co-founded. We provide client and product solutions for network and cyber security analytics/monitoring. We work closely with Enterprise Networks, Service Providers, Network Operators, Government, System Integrators and OEM clients to deploy robust solutions meeting their requirements.

Gestionnaire de projet spécialisé en contenu culturel et numérique, Sven rejoint la FCCF en 2022 pour propulser une des actions majeures liées à la Politique du Québec en matière de francophonie canadienne : L'accélérateur TADA. Sven agit en tant que courroie de transmission entre les membres de la FCCF et les multiples organismes partenaires de la francophonie canadienne, acadienne et québécoise.

biography:
Avec plus de 20 ans d'expérience, Michel Bourque est reconnu pour son expertise en gestion de projets dans le secteur des technologies de l'information, notamment dans le domaine de la cybersécurité. Il n'est pas à son premier succès entrepreneurial. Avant de fonder CYBERDEFENSE.AI, il a réussi à transformer une PME en quatre ans, passant d'un chiffre d'affaires de 500 000$ à une organisation spécialisée dans la cybersécurité des systèmes industriels critiques avec des revenus de 6 millions de dollars.

Le projet CYBERDEFENSE.AI va bien au-delà d'une simple entreprise. C'est une initiative qui réunit des expertises diverses pour créer une plateforme novatrice, exploitant les nouvelles technologies pour relever les défis croissants de la cybersécurité.

La plateforme CYBERDEFENSE.AI a été conçue pour automatiser la protection, la surveillance et la conformité des infrastructures web. Notre plateforme exploite la technologie de l'IA pour automatiser la détection des applications couramment utilisées dans le domaine de la santé.

CYBERDEFENSE.AI s'intègre aux centres de données privés pour accéder au marché du cloud privé, permettant la collecte de données qui alimentent les modèles d'IA pour le profilage des applications, la correction virtuelle et la détection des menaces, prévenant ainsi les incidents de cybersécurité.

Denis is a partner and patent agent in Gowling WLG's Montreal office, where he works in the Intellectual Property group. His practice covers all things patent, including the strategic acquisition of patents in areas such as artificial intelligence, fintech, medical devices, software and telecommunications. With 20 years of IP experience in Canada, the United States, France and the United Kingdom, he worked in the United Kingdom for a considerable part of his career, including as an associate in the one of the largest IP firms in Europe. Denis also worked at a well-known technology company, where he was responsible for growing the European optical networking patent portfolio. Before entering private practice, Denis was a patent examiner at the Canadian Intellectual Property Office and the United Kingdom Intellectual Property Office.

Fort de 20 années d’expérience en PI au Canada, aux États-Unis, en France et au Royaume-Uni, il a œuvré au Royaume-Uni pendant une partie considérable de sa carrière, notamment à titre d’associé au sein de l’un des plus importants cabinets de PI d’Europe. biography: When brands like Google, Starbucks, Shopify and GE want to leverage technology to better connect with their consumers, they call Mitch Joel. He has been called “one of North America’s leading visionaries” and the “Rock Star of Digital Marketing” by Strategy Magazine, but he is much more than that. Mitch Joel is founder of Six Pixels Group—an advisory, investing and content producing company that's focused on commerce and innovation (although he prefers the title "Media Hacker"). Prior to Six Pixels Group, Mitch spent close to two decades building, running and (eventually) selling his business. He was president of Mirum—a global digital marketing agency operating in 25 countries with close to 3,000 employees. Mirum is owned by WPP. Mitch has been named one of the top 100 online marketers in the world, and was awarded the highly prestigious Top 40 Under 40. Mitch's first book, "Six Pixels Of Separation," named after his successful blog and podcast, is a business and marketing best-seller. His second book, "CTRL ALT Delete," was named one of the best business books of 2013 by Amazon. Mitch is frequently called upon to be a subject matter expert for publications like Fast Company, Strategy, Forbes, The Globe & Mail and many others. He is a columnist and journalist for the Harvard Business Review, Inc. magazine, The Huffington Post and many other magazines and newspapers. Mitch speaks frequently to diverse groups like Wal-Mart, Starbucks, Microsoft, Procter and Gamble, Twitter, Unilever and every organization and association in between. Since 2005, he has given anywhere between 40–60 keynote presentations a year. Mitch is also the host of Groove – The No Treble Podcast, where he is slowly trying to build the largest oral history of electric bass players in the world

Kris Krüg is a cultural technologist, creative entrepreneur, community organizer, and Founder of the BC + AI Ecosystem Association.

With over two decades of experience in technology, media, and the arts, Kris has been instrumental in building Vancouver’s grassroots AI community, organizing monthly meetups that have drawn more than 2,000 participants. He is also the co-founder and president of The AI Upgrade, where he develops AI training programs for professionals across sectors.

Kris’s leadership emphasizes ethical, inclusive, and practical approaches to AI, and he is recognized for championing public-interest technology that centers people and communities over products and hype. He has advised governments, universities, and industry leaders on the responsible adoption of AI, drawing from both technical expertise and deep community engagement.

In practice, Kris works on the ground where theory meets deployment: supporting SMEs with AI adoption, developing applied training curricula, and mapping BC’s AI ecosystem as a living network of researchers, startups, and civil society ￼. He has led initiatives around AI literacy, workforce transition, and open-source adoption — helping ensure the province’s AI future is both competitive and equitable.

Known half-jokingly as a “professional troublemaker in AI policy circles,” Kris wears the label as a badge of honour. What it really signals is his refusal to play along with hype, grift, or top-down narratives that don’t serve people on the ground. His “man of the people” approach — showing up in community halls, coffee shops, and meetups instead of just boardrooms — has made him a trusted connector across disciplines. That same approach can make professional grifters nervous, but it’s also what earns genuine buy-in from the diverse communities shaping BC’s AI future.

At his core, Kris believes that AI should strengthen trust, resilience, and opportunity in BC — not just efficiency. His work is focused on making sure this technology reflects the values of the people it serves, while keeping BC on the map as a global hub for applied, ethical, and future-facing AI.

biography:
Lisa Lambert is on a mission to shape a more innovative and prosperous future for Canada.

In her current role as the inaugural CEO of Quantum Industry Canada (QIC), Lisa stands at the forefront of the country's quantum leap. Her force-multiplying leadership is guiding the collective efforts across the QIC community to unlock the potential of this critical technology sector that’s projected to contribute up to 3% of Canada’s GDP and generate over 200,000 jobs by 2045.

Globally, Lisa's deep commitment to advancing transformative innovation has earned her a spot on the International Advisory Board for Japan’s new Global Research and Development Center for Business by Quantum-AI Technology. Closer to home, she’s dedicated to nurturing the next generation of Canadian innovators and entrepreneurs as a mentor with YELL Canada.

Before her tenure at QIC, Lisa's career was marked by her leadership in forward-thinking initiatives at the intersection of science, technology, and society. She’s spearheaded numerous trailblazing global projects, working in collaboration with some of the brightest minds and top organizations worldwide.

Lisa also made her mark as the co-author of "The Future Is Trust," a book that has resonated globally, becoming an Amazon bestseller and #1 Hot New Release across several markets. Her practical insights into trust-centered leadership have influenced how leaders across the world think and act.

Lisa's mantra? The future's bright, and it's ours to shape. She's committed to making sure we all get there together, unlocking new possibilities along the way.

From July 2016 until September 2020, Dr. Bohn was the Director of the Data Architecture & Engineering group in the Corp. During this time, he formed a high-performing team of data experts, established a unified data architecture, supported digital business initiatives with data modeling and engineering services, and delivered the global Schaeffler Big Data & Analytics Platform on the Microsoft Azure Cloud. 

Since October 2020, Dr. Bohn is the Head of the Innovation Cluster for Artificial Intelligence & Data Science in the Schaeffler Corporate R&D department. He now closely collaborates with business units worldwide on enhancing Schaeffler products and digital services for automotive and industry customers through AI and machine learning methods. The spectrum of AI applications ranges from mechatronic products and systems for automated driving, e-mobility and robotics over IoT services to digital Mobility 4.0 and Industry 4.0 solutions in the Cloud.

I’ve learned that enterprises don’t fail because of a lack of ideas—they fail because their systems can’t keep up. I’ve watched teams drown in reports while the real problems—churn, missed forecasts, stalled growth—go unsolved.

That’s why I founded Predicte. My work is about building systems that act, not just report. I take an FDE-style approach, embedding predictive and prescriptive intelligence directly into workflows so businesses can see what’s happening, understand why, and know exactly what to do next.

Before this, I spent over 25 years leading digital transformation and ERP projects—so yes, I’ve seen every way a system can go sideways. I’m also an engineer with an MBA, which basically means I can do the math and make a PowerPoint about it.

For me, it’s not about dashboards—it’s about outcomes. Helping leaders replace guesswork with foresight, so they can build momentum and scale with confidence. Lets connect!

biography:
Lucas Russell is the founder and CEO of Goverly.ai, the Canadian startup that decided government procurement didn’t have to be a maze designed by Kafka and managed by Excel. Goverly is building an AI-powered platform that helps businesses instantly understand RFPs, grants, and contract opportunities, then match with the right government program—provincial, territorial, or federal. In short: Goverly turns bureaucratic headache into business opportunity.

With Goverly Defence, Lucas is tackling one of Canada’s most complex puzzles: Industrial and Technological Benefits (ITBs). Instead of forcing prime contractors and SMEs to slog through endless paperwork, Goverly Defence automates the matchmaking and compliance, helping both sides meet obligations faster, cheaper, and with fewer grey hairs.

Before Goverly, Lucas built and exited ventures in fintech, health tech, and AI services, each time refining his knack for turning impossible processes into usable products. His past work taught him how to navigate regulatory hurdles, translate technical complexity into plain English, and—most importantly—spot when a system is so broken it’s begging to be rebuilt. Goverly is the culmination of that pattern: a platform born from years of staring at government contracts and asking, “why does it have to be this hard?”

Lucas has pitched on international stages, worked alongside provincial and federal governments, and convinced investors, bureaucrats, and skeptics alike that AI can actually make government easier to work with. He’s known for his ability to blend sharp strategy with humor—because nothing makes procurement reform more palatable than a well-timed joke about compliance checklists.

Outside of Goverly, Lucas is a Canadian entrepreneur who has coached novice soccer teams, tested more startup ideas than most people test coffee blends, and built a reputation for asking “why not?” at the exact moment others are listing reasons why not. His approach to entrepreneurship is equal parts fearless, practical, and mischievous.

At this conference, Lucas isn’t just here to talk about Goverly (though he will happily demo how AI can chew through a hundred-page RFP in seconds). He’s here to connect with fellow builders, researchers, and policy thinkers who share his obsession with taking AI out of the lab and into the messiest, most consequential corners of the real world.

If you want to discuss AI for procurement, sovereign tech, defence, or government innovation, Lucas will have ideas. If you want to talk soccer strategy, Canadian small-cap markets, or the best way to pitch a room full of skeptics, he’ll have stories. And if you just want to laugh about the absurdity of government paperwork while secretly believing it can be fixed—he’s definitely your guy.

⸻

⚡ Disclaimer: conversations with Lucas may result in new startup ideas, unexpected collaborations, or sudden optimism about government actually working better.

biography:
As the Trade Commissioner responsible for Foreign Direct Investment (FDI) in AI and Financial Services, my primary focus is showcasing the vast investment opportunities Canada, and Quebec, has to offer. My pursuit of the MMAI program at Smith's School of Business at Queen's University further enhances my professional insights, providing a holistic understanding of Canada's vibrant AI ecosystem.

Our nation's AI infrastructure stands strong, backed by world-class institutions such as Mila, Vector Institute, and Amii, and foundational educational pillars like Smith's at Queen's University and countless other universities across the country. The collaboration between academia, government, and the public sector crafts a conducive environment for investment, nurturing innovation, and fostering sustainable growth.

To the international multinational community: Canada's AI and Financial Services sectors are brimming with untapped potential. Connecting with me is your gateway to navigating and capitalizing on these opportunities, aligning your investment aspirations and corporate goals with Canada's unparalleled assets. If Canada is on your investment radar, I warmly invite you to get in touch. Together, we can shape and bring your vision to life, ensuring unparalleled success in the evolving AI landscape.

En tant que Délégué Commercial responsable de l'Investissement Étranger Direct (IED) en Intelligence Artificielle et Services Financiers, mon rôle principal est de mettre en évidence la multitude d'opportunités d'investissement que le Canada, et en particulier le Québec, offre. La solide formation académique que j'ai acquise grâce au programme MMAI à la Smith's School of Business de l'Université Queen's vient compléter mes connaissances professionnelles, offrant une compréhension exhaustive de l'écosystème dynamique de l'IA au Canada.

L'infrastructure IA de notre pays est à la fois diversifiée et solide, ancrée dans des institutions de classe mondiale telles que Mila, Vector Institute, et Amii, ainsi que dans des établissements éducatifs renommés comme Smith's à l'Université Queen's et de nombreux autres piliers académiques à travers le pays. Cette synergie collaborative, reliant l'académie, le gouvernement et le secteur public, crée un environnement propice à l'investissement, favorisant l'innovation et stimulant une croissance durable.

À la communauté des multinationales internationales: les secteurs de l'IA et des Services Financiers du Canada regorgent de potentiel inexploité. Se connecter avec moi est votre passerelle pour naviguer et capitaliser sur ces opportunités, en alignant vos ambitions d'investissement et les objectifs de votre entreprise avec les atouts inégalés du Canada. Si le Canada figure sur votre radar d'investissement, je vous invite chaleureusement à me contacter. Ensemble, nous pourrons façonner et réaliser votre vision, garantissant un succès sans précédent dans le paysage évolutif de l'IA.

biography:
David Kershaw
Founder, No-Code Engineering
nocodeengineering.io 

David Kershaw is the founder of No-Code Engineering, a company focused on governing automation systems at scale. For nearly a decade he has worked as a high-autonomy contractor in enterprise environments, stabilizing fragile automations and introducing governance frameworks where they were missing.

His specialization is no-code and low-code orchestration — platforms such as Workfront Fusion and Make.com — where automation estates expand quickly but oversight often lags. David’s approach centers on blueprint-native interrogation and automated design governance. Instead of waiting for failures in production, he works at the design layer to surface risks around complexity, environment separation, pagination, and scalability before they reach the business.

This philosophy underpins his current product development: tools that make automation flows more legible, interrogable, and governable. By focusing on design-time governance, these tools give organizations visibility into risks that would otherwise remain hidden inside sprawling automation footprints.

In parallel, David publishes essays and system notes at nocodeengineering.io, where he writes about automation governance, scale challenges, and enterprise system clarity. His emphasis is on substance over optics — building automation systems that reflect how businesses actually work, not just how they appear on dashboards.

David has been invited to speak at ecosystem events, contribute to AI and automation conferences, and participate in accelerator programs aimed at formalizing governance tooling for the next wave of enterprise automation.

Based in Fredericton, New Brunswick, David balances his professional work with family life and ongoing exploration of system design at scale.

biography: Pamela Snively is the Chief Data & Trust Officer at TELUS. She leads the team responsible for privacy governance and data ethics, along with data management and a number of compliance functions, including the Anti-bribery & Corruption and Competition Law programs. Pam approaches overall data governance through the lens of customer trust, leveraging TELUS’ CustomerFirst principle to drive the organization’s commitment to privacy and data ethics.Pam is a lawyer but has dedicated most of her career to developing and operationalizing privacy best practices, either as a consultant or in-house. Under Pam’s leadership, TELUS has significantly transformed its approach to transparency about its data handling practices. This has included a refresh of the TELUS Privacy Centre to include layered information on TELUS' datamanagement practices, as well as some best practices to help our customers protect their information. Pam has also published the framework for her privacy management program online, encouraging TELUS’ customers to more fully understand what responsible private sector organizations do to protect privacy.Pamela was the recipient of the 2017 Ontario Bar Association’s Karen Spector Memorial Award for Excellence in Privacy Law. She participates in a number of national and international think-tanks and governance bodies related to privacy and data governance, including serving as a Board member for the Information Accountability Foundation and on the Privacy and Data Advisory Committee for the Canadian Marketing Association. She is also a founding member and Chair of Canada’s Business Privacy Group, a working group made up of some of Canada’s leading privacy professionals and industry associations focused on building trust in Canada’s digital ecosystem and legislative regime.Pam is a frequent speaker on privacy and data ethics and she actively encourages other organizations to join her in her mission to earn and elevate consumer trust in our digital ecosystem.

biography:
Working as a Dental Surgeon and clinic owner by day, and a PhD candidate in A.I. at Université Paris Cité by night. I operate at the convergence of clinical practice and deep learning.

My research explores the potential of repurposing routine dental radiographs for opportunistic health screening. By developing advanced A.I. models, I aim to extract biomarkers for systemic conditions, such as osteoporosis, from this commonly available imaging data. The ultimate objective is to establish a low-cost, scalable method for early disease detection that integrates seamlessly into existing healthcare workflows.

Firmly believing that research must lead to tangible solutions, I am also an entrepreneur in the health-tech space. I focus on building businesses that can take promising AI models, like the ones in my research, from the lab to the clinic, ensuring they deliver real value to doctors and patients.

l am here at ALL IN to connect with fellow innovators passionate about building clinically-relevant A.I. solutions. If you're interested in medical imaging, predictive analytics, or shaping the future of diagnostics, I would love to start a conversation.

biography:
Brett is a recognized innovation leadership expert. As an organizational psychologist, consultant and researcher, he adds a unique psychodynamic perspective to manage the tricky aspects of innovation and change. He serves as a trustworthy thought partner to senior executives in central banks, leading corporates, tier 1 consultancies and high-growth startups.

Originally trained as an economist while also an athlete and then coach in Canada’s Olympic development system, his approach has always been grounded in business realities and the psychology of high performance. As recognized by over 200 awards and patents when he served as an innovation leader living in Vancouver, Paris and London—working with innovators like Apple, Google, Jaguar Land Rover, AMEX, Barclays, Diageo and Unilever.

In 2019, he sharpened his leadership development practice at INSEAD—the leading global business school based in Fontainebleau, France. During the three-year Executive Master of Change (systems psychodynamics), Brett focused his research on the psychology of effective innovation leadership—receiving distinction in 2021. A product of this research, The Innovation Leadership Map (ILM) has become a powerful leadership development tool to help professionals more effectively achieve higher impact, healthier teams and happier careers.

Brett has a specialist interest in treating impulse control, burnout and loss of confidence from workplace challenges such as excessive expectations or permanent frustration. Symptoms that are often addressed by ILM and clinical leadership development programs for more positive professional and personal outcomes.

Outside his private practice, Brett advises the G20 Leaders Summit on digital leaders, is an advisory-backed investor with Working Title Capital and is a board advisor. Socially, he cycles as an official Rapha Cycle Club, enjoys alpine pursuits and loves good food. Vancouver based, globally active!

Process Improvement Consultant at TELUS, where I focus on leveraging AI and business process frameworks to make complex systems feel clearer, lighter, and more scalable. That means thinking beyond the technology itself and designing the connective tissue that allows teams, tools and strategies to flow together seamlessly.

My perspective is shaped by a mix of rigor and creativity: I draw on Lean Six Sigma discipline, BPMN process modeling, context engineering and structured governance frameworks while also embracing design thinking and imaginative exploration. Outside my corporate role, I'm equally passionate about how AI can empower founders, leaders, and independent creators. biography:
Tuyen Vo has been working with successful entrepreneurs for nearly 20 years. She currently heads Technology and Innovation Banking for National Bank of Canada. Among the big six banks of systemic importance in the country, National Bank is the only one headquartered in the province of Quebec and the only one with a female leader at the helm of its Technology lending practice. Since joining the Bank in 2019, Tuyen has contributed to tripling revenues and quadrupling her business volumes through successful expansion of her group across the country. In 2023, she has been instrumental in the acquisition of the commercial loan portfolio of Silicon Valley Bank’s Canadian branch, with the effect of further accelerating the Bank’s Technology and Innovation Banking group presence across Canada.

Prior to joining National Bank, Tuyen held leadership roles within the retail, corporate banking and credit risk divisions at two major Canadian banks. She is most proud of the strong and engaged teams she’s built along the way.

Tuyen has served on the Bank’s Inclusion & Diversity Council as the Women segment Lead since 2020. In this capacity, she co-sponsored the launch of an innovative Sponsorship program that earned National Bank the top recognition in the Equity-Diversity-Inclusion category in a prestigious 2023 HR Award. Tuyen also sits on the LPAC of Accelia Capital, a venture capital fund that invests in innovative companies owned or led by women. She’s also involved with many causes aligned with her convictions and expertise, including education, the fight against poverty and helping immigrants transition to a new country. In 2023, she was awarded by Women We Admire as one of The Top 50 Women Leaders of Montreal for 2023.

Tuyen holds a finance degree from HEC Montréal, including a stint at the Institut d’Études Politiques de Paris (Sciences Pô). Having lived on four continents, Tuyen is fluent in three languages and can order a coffee in five more.

During the COVID-19 pandemic, Dr. Kamya provided due diligence around AI tools for investment banks and was introduced to Insilico Medicine and its AI drug discovery platform, Pharma.AI, which includes novel target discovery (PandaOmics), novel small molecule design (Chemistry42) and clinical trial prediction (InClinico). She saw the potential of Insilico’s platform to optimize drug design with speed and efficiency and to meaningfully improve the drug discovery process. She joined the team in August 2020, initially leading its Chemistry42 platform. She holds a PhD in Chemistry from Concordia University.

biography:
“Technology and marketing for good". That’s how I would summarize the core of my professional drive.

I’ve always been fascinated with exploration. Space exploration, in particular, has been a constant source of amazement since I first set eyes on the stars. I followed my passion and specialized on technology planning for space projects. I continue to work on technology roadmapping for future space exploration missions, working mostly with government sector clients.

Over the years, I discovered another passion: building web experiences that deliver value and a bit of fun to our everyday existence. After I learned how to build web applications, I focused on a much more difficult challenge: building teams that can do a much better job than I ever could. Today, thanks to the dedicated work of my team, we have two web applications that serve thousands of users every month. Plumfind.com is our AI-enabled business intelligence platform for fashion. Whatnextnow.com is our personal recommender app for consumers.

The final source of inspiration is digital marketing. Even though I studied marketing at university, it took me a few decades to understand how much power the entire discipline holds. It can be used for manipulating opinions and creating a very unhealthy view of the world. But it can also be used for good. Through my digital marketing agency, I had the pleasure of working with more than one hundred clients.

Feel free to contact me if you are also interested in the areas I mentioned above. I'd love to hear from you.

I'm especially interested in AI applications in B2B settings. Climate action, renewable energy, sustainability in fashion are some of my particular areas of interest.

biography:
Dario Zujo is the Director of Business Development at Zilia, a Canadian medical technology company developing a platform to non-invasively measure biomarkers through the eye.

Zilia’s first product, the Zilia Ocular, is designed to capture retinal images and assess oxygen saturation in the eye. The technology aims to equip eye care professionals with new tools to explore the potential of ocular biomarkers in support of clinical decision-making.

At Zilia, Dario leads commercial strategy, including distribution development, clinical collaborations, and implementation of educational tools to support early users. He works closely with eye care professionals to ensure the technology is introduced in a way that aligns with the needs of clinical practice.

Zilia is currently collaborating with academic and clinical partners in North America and Asia as part of its ongoing validation and market readiness efforts.

Maxime est un entrepreneur intuitif dont le parcours est marqué par la créativité, la stratégie, l’optimisation et la transformation d’entreprises. Après un parcours universitaire en affaires, il a co-fondé la maison de production vidéo La Raffinerie. Il y a bâti et dirigé une équipe créative qui a collaboré avec certaines des plus importantes entreprises canadiennes.

À la suite d’un processus de fusion-acquisition avec une agence de publicité bien établie, Maxime a élargi son rôle vers le développement stratégique et organisationnel, consolidant son expertise dans la compréhension des réalités clients afin de proposer des solutions créatives et pertinentes à des enjeux complexes d’affaires.

Aujourd’hui chez Vooban, il accompagne les organisations d’envergure dans leurs projets d’innovation et de transformation numérique. Fort d’un parcours différent de l’univers des technologies, il apporte une touche rafraîchissante de créativité et un regard externe qui enrichissent les réflexions stratégiques. Être un « outsider » lui permet autant à l’interne qu’auprès des clients de challenger les perspectives établies et de transformer cette différence en véritable valeur ajoutée. Convaincant et pertinent, il sait se faire rapidement une place autour de la table des exécutifs, où il agit comme un allié stratégique, en alliant vision, innovation et résultats concrets.

--

Maxime is an intuitive entrepreneur whose career has been defined by creativity, strategy, business optimization, and organizational transformation. After completing a business degree, he co-founded the video production house La Raffinerie, where he built and led a creative team that partnered with some of Canada’s most prominent companies.

Following a merger and acquisition process with a well-established advertising agency, Maxime expanded his role into strategic and organizational development, strengthening his expertise in understanding client realities and delivering creative, relevant solutions to complex business challenges.

Today at Vooban, he partners with large-scale organizations on their innovation and digital transformation initiatives. Coming from outside the traditional tech world, Maxime brings a refreshing dose of creativity and an external perspective that challenge the status quo and create real value for clients. His outsider’s viewpoint is a strength both internally and externally, enabling him to quickly earn his place at the executive table, where he acts as a trusted ally, combining vision, innovation, and tangible business impact.

biography:
Motivé par l’économie numérique depuis des années et expert dans le domaine, je travaille à en comprendre les impacts sur nos sociétés civile et civique, afin de bâtir une société numérique aussi riche que respectueuse.

Œuvrant dans le monde des services professionnels en technologie depuis plus de 30 ans, j'ai bâti ma notoriété et mon image, à la fois comme employé de cabinets conseil, comme entrepreneur (notamment avec le tout premier événement sur le commerce électronique en 2010 - eCOM Montréal) ou comme consultant et administrateur d’OBNL.

J'ai aussi la chance d'être chroniqueur régulier pour le balado « Mon Carnet » de Bruno Guglielminetti (sur les sujets liés à l’économie numérique), ainsi que pour Pierre-Olivier Zappa sur la chaîne TVA (pour les sujets d’actualité liés à l’intelligence artificielle).

Je publie également à l'occasion dans d’autres médias comme La Presse et enfin, suis l’auteur du livre “Vos clics. Leur cash.” (que je vous invite à acheter et lire :-) ) dans lequel j'ouvre le débat quant à la vétusté de nos modèles fiscaux à l’ère d’une économie numérique prépondérante.

Philip est avocat, programmeur et conseiller en technologies prédictives et IA au Barreau du Québec, où il se consacre à l’encadrement de l’utilisation de l’IA dans la pratique juridique, avec un accent particulier sur la gouvernance de l’IA, la formation, le développement et l'utilisation éthique et responsable d’outils d’IA, ainsi que sur la sensibilisation du public aux enjeux que l’IA pose dans le domaine du droit.

Grâce à une formation sur l'IA responsable et les droits humains à Mila, il a approfondi ses connaissances théoriques et pratiques sur les enjeux éthiques, juridiques, politiques et socio-techniques émergents à l'intersection de l’IA et des droits fondamentaux.

Avant de rejoindre le Barreau, Philip a été coordonnateur et développeur de projets IA. Dans ce rôle, il a contribué au développement d’applications d’IA génératives pour le secteur juridique, renforçant ainsi l'innovation technologique au service de la justice.

biography:
Make bigger business decisions. Better.

Over a span of 25 years in the visual effects (VFX) industry, I've had the privilege of contributing to many memorable movies and TV shows, leveraging my background in fine arts, business, and industrial engineering to lead teams at top North American VFX studios. This journey instilled a profound understanding of storytelling through visuals, a skill I've come to realize has much in common with another passion of mine: simplifying complex business decisions.

The leap from VFX to tech entrepreneurship might seem wide, but the thread connecting them is visual storytelling. In VFX, we use visuals to make complex narratives understandable and engaging. I saw an opportunity to apply this approach to the often rigid and inaccessible world of financial modeling. Traditional business planning tools, dominated by spreadsheets, lacked the flexibility and intuitiveness that a more visual approach could offer. This realization sparked the idea for whatifi.

Management struggles with countless high-stakes decisions.

Cash flow. Capacity planning. SaaS pricing. Fundraising. Debt. M&A. Growth. Churn. 

whatifi is born from a desire to revolutionize how businesses approach financial modeling and strategic planning. Our ecosystem helps decision-makers to create visual "what if" scenarios, making it easier to understand the potential outcomes of different business decisions. It's designed to be intuitive, leveraging a decision-tree methodology that visually maps out complex decision paths and outcomes. This approach not only makes financial planning more accessible but also fosters collaboration and creativity among team members.

As the founder of whatifi, my goal is to bridge the gap between the dynamic, visual logic of VFX and the strategic needs of business planning. We've built whatifi to help entrepreneurs and business leaders visualize the impact of their decisions in a way that's as engaging and informative as a well-crafted story. It's a tool that reflects my journey from creating compelling visuals on screen to enabling businesses to paint their futures with broader, more informed strokes.

In pitching whatifi, I'm not just introducing a new product; I'm advocating for a shift in how we approach business planning and decision-making. It's a journey from the creative confines of VFX studios to the entrepreneurial challenge of redefining an industry. And it's just beginning.

biography:
I’m an immigration lawyer who decided the old way of doing things wasn’t good enough. After a decade in legal practice—spanning Common Law (J.D.) and Civil Law (LL.B.), managing firms, litigating, and closing over $1M in immigration service sales—I hit the same wall every immigration professional knows: outdated tools, manual workflows, and a model that scales costs instead of results.

Rather than hire more staff to patch the problem, I built a new model. Enter Immigratio—a proprietary, AI-driven case management platform designed to automate up to 85% of immigration workflows for lawyers and licensed consultants. Born out of my own firm’s pain points, Immigratio isn’t just software—it’s a re-engineering of how immigration cases are prepared, filed, and managed across Canadian and U.S. jurisdictions.

As NAIA’s co-founder and head of product vision, I fuse my deep legal expertise with a relentless focus on real-world application. My dual training and hands-on experience managing both Common Law and Civil Law cases mean Immigratio is built to work seamlessly in multiple legal systems. The platform’s AI automates document collection, form completion, and compliance checks, while giving lawyers more time to focus on high-value strategy instead of clerical grind.

In under two years, we’ve gone from concept to active beta with 10 law firms and consultants—over 200 real cases processed through the platform. The impact? Measurable time savings, lower error rates, and an entirely new way to scale legal practice without scaling overhead.

I’m not here to replace lawyers. I’m here to make them radically more effective—turning AI into an everyday ally for legal professionals. At ALL IN 2025, I’m sharing how we took a traditional, paper-heavy legal process and rebuilt it into an AI-powered, future-proof workflow—one that’s already transforming immigration law practice.

_------------------------------------------------

Je suis avocat spécialisé en droit de l'immigration et j'ai décidé que l'ancienne façon de faire ne suffisait plus. Après une décennie de pratique juridique, couvrant la common law (J.D.) et le droit civil (LL.B.), la gestion de cabinets, le contentieux et la clôture de plus d'un million de dollars de ventes de services d'immigration, je me suis heurté au même obstacle que tout professionnel de l'immigration : des outils obsolètes, des flux de travail manuels et un modèle qui ajuste les coûts au détriment des résultats.

Plutôt que d'embaucher du personnel pour résoudre le problème, j'ai créé un nouveau modèle. Voici Immigratio, une plateforme exclusive de gestion de dossiers basée sur l'IA, conçue pour automatiser jusqu'à 85 % des flux de travail en matière d'immigration pour les avocats et les consultants agréés. Née des difficultés rencontrées par mon propre cabinet, Immigratio n'est pas qu'un simple logiciel : c'est une refonte de la préparation, du dépôt et de la gestion des dossiers d'immigration au Canada et aux États-Unis.

En tant que cofondateur et responsable de la vision produit de NAIA, je combine ma solide expertise juridique à une attention constante portée à l'application concrète. Ma double formation et mon expérience pratique de la gestion de dossiers de common law et de droit civil permettent à Immigratio de fonctionner de manière transparente dans de nombreux systèmes juridiques. L'IA de la plateforme automatise la collecte de documents, le remplissage des formulaires et les contrôles de conformité, tout en laissant aux avocats plus de temps pour se concentrer sur des stratégies à forte valeur ajoutée plutôt que sur des tâches administratives fastidieuses.

En moins de deux ans, nous sommes passés du concept à la version bêta active avec 10 cabinets d'avocats et consultants ; plus de 200 dossiers réels ont été traités via la plateforme. L'impact ? Des gains de temps mesurables, une réduction des taux d'erreur et une toute nouvelle façon de développer la pratique juridique sans augmenter les frais généraux.

Je ne suis pas là pour remplacer les avocats. Je suis là pour les rendre radicalement plus efficaces, en faisant de l'IA un allié au quotidien des professionnels du droit. Lors de la conférence ALL IN 2025, je partage comment nous avons transformé un processus juridique traditionnel, lourd en papier, en un flux de travail pérenne et optimisé par l'IA, qui transforme déjà la pratique du droit de l'immigration.

biography:
My passion for building MemreeAI started in 2024 with a burning desire to use my knowledge and skills to make a difference in people's lives. So I dropped out of my PhD program after one year because I didn't see my research making an impact on anyone's lives, and I founded Memree. Since then, it's been an arduous journey full of heartbreaks, rejections, sleepless nights, panic, stress, and some good news here and there. But will I choose any other life than this? HELL NO. I have lived the first 30 years of my life building things for others and living a mundane yet comfortable life. And through the first 30 years of my lived experience, I realised that, that life is not for me. I always knew that I wanted to be an entrepreneur. I knew I had the risk appetite, the hunger for building something greater than me, the hunger for excellence, and the passion to build things that help others. I just didn't have the courage to make the move earlier. I needed a "point-of-no-return". That came in the form of getting fired from a job, massive credit card debt, and severe anxiety. I knew this was my calling to make a move. And now, despite all the hardships, I know why I chose this life. Because I am meant to be an entrepreneur. This is who I am. I don't seek comfort, I don't seek safety. All I want is to make a company that will outlast me, will feed hundreds (if not thousands) of families who work for the company. I would consider that a life well lived.

Being part of the NEXT AI was one of our biggest achievements. And now being able to present our passion in front of thousands of people in the ALL IN event is magical. 

In this journey, I also found my co-founder, Karen Southwell, who keeps me in check and keeps our company moving in the right direction. Without her, Memree and I would both be lost.

biography:
Growing up in Canada, studying in the US and the UK, and working in China have broadened my perspective and fueled my passion for creating positive change. I believe every challenge is an opportunity to innovate and make a lasting impact.

My Entrepreneurial Path

- Early Start: At 19, I launched my journey by running a painting franchise, developing key sales and leadership skills.
- Diverse Ventures: My venture into Fairtrade coffee was tough yet enlightening, setting the stage for even greater challenges.
- First Success: At 21, I co-founded Ibboo and introduced an innovative travel pillow that secured a deal on Quebec’s Shark Tank (Dans l’oeil du Dragon) and led me to represent Canada at the G20 YEA summit in Japan.
- Global Expansion: Relocating to Shenzhen, China allowed me to work closely with suppliers and gain invaluable insights into international trade and cross-cultural collaboration.

Pivoting with Purpose

Inspired by China’s efficiency and the urgent need for transparent pricing during the COVID-19 pandemic, I assembled a team in 2020 to develop the first version of the eezly app as a food delivery price comparison tool. With rising inflation in 2022, we shifted our focus to grocery price comparison, rebuilding our platform from the ground up to address everyday consumer challenges.

eezly: Making life more affordable

Based in Montreal, our mission at eezly is to make life more affordable and empower consumers with easy access to essential data. By comparing prices across thousands of products at major retailers, our users can optimize their savings—potentially cutting their grocery bills by up to 50%. We are committed to helping families save money, promoting economic sustainability, and strengthening community financial security.

I’m always eager to connect with people to discuss innovative solutions.
Visit eezly.com to learn more about what we're building, or feel free to connect if you’d like to chat!

biography:
Tu veux gagner du temps, créer des visuels qui captent l’attention et comprendre comment l’IA peut simplifier ton quotidien professionnel? C’est exactement ce que je fais.

Je suis formatrice numérique, Canvassador et créatrice d’outils IA. Depuis 2018, j’accompagne entrepreneur·es, OBNL et PME à maîtriser Canva, et depuis 2023, je les aide à adopter l’IA de façon responsable, éthique et sécuritaire.


Ce que j’apporte:

- Formation numérique accessible : démystifier Canva et l’IA avec des explications simples.
- Expertise Canva Équipe : structurer ton espace collaboratif pour plus de fluidité et d’efficacité.
- Création de GPTs et agents IA personnalisés : intégrer des assistants virtuels conçus pour tes besoins réels.
- Accompagnement en gouvernance IA : t’assurer que tes usages respectent les bonnes pratiques éthiques.


Pourquoi travailler avec moi?

- Parce que je rends la technologie simple, pratique et humaine.
- Parce que je crois qu’innover, ce n’est pas seulement utiliser des outils, c’est savoir les apprivoiser.
- Et parce que chaque formation est construite pour être utile dès le lendemain.

Si tu veux développer ton autonomie numérique, créer du contenu qui fait briller ta marque et explorer l’IA de façon responsable, écris-moi. Ensemble, on fera rayonner ta vision.

biography:
Martin A. Bader is a European and Swiss Patent Attorney and a representative before the Unified Patent Court (UPC). Currently he is staying as an Adjunct Professor at McGill University in Montréal and is an Associate Member to the McGill Centre for Intellectual Property Policy.

As well as being Managing Partner and Founder of the specialized innovation and intellectual property management advisory group BGW IP GmbH St. Gallen, he is Full Professor for Technology Management and Entrepreneurship at the University of Applied Sciences Ingolstadt (THI), Bavaria/Germany. Previously, he was Vice President and Chief Intellectual Property Officer at Infineon Technologies, Munich, incl. its IPO, and Head of the Intellectual Property Management Competence Center at the Institute of Technology Management at the University of St. Gallen (HSG).

He is a mediator at the Mediation Center for Alternative Dispute Resolution at the World Intellectual Property Organization (WIPO) and has for many years been regarded as being among the top 300 intellectual property strategists worldwide according to the Intellectual Asset Management magazine’s IAM strategy 300 index. He is also a long-standing author of numerous specialist publications and an internationally sought-after speaker in the field of intellectual property management.

📢 Barcelona ranks 3rd worldwide for attracting foreign investment in hashtag#AI, according to IBM’s Global Location Trends 2025.

👉 Only behind London and Singapore, Barcelona is also the leading AI investment hub in the EU.

💬 Jaume Baró Torres, CEO of Catalonia Trade & Investment, highlighted: “Catalonia is a leading destination for technology-driven investment projects, particularly in the strategically important field of artificial intelligence.”

With nearly 500 AI companies, over 160 international tech hubs, and a fast-growing talent pool, Catalonia is consolidating its position as one of the world’s most dynamic hashtag#AI ecosystems.

🔗 Read more about this recognition: https://lnkd.in/dhACMdZS

Let's meet in person to discuss your European expansion projects.

As Executive Director for the Catalonia Trade & Investment Office in Montreal since 2007, I have helped hundreds of Catalan companies establish trade, technology and investment relations with Canadian businesses in a variety of sectors, in addition to facilitating Canadian business interests in the Catalonia.

biography:
Working in the human resources field for over 20 years, Etienne has supported numerous organizations in projects aimed at optimizing their compensation infrastructure and led work teams on complex projects with a wide range of organizations and sector groups. Holding a master's degree in human resources management from HEC Montréal, a master's degree in training management from the Université de Sherbrooke, and an executive program in Artificial Intelligence from the MIT Sloan School of Management, he joined Normandin Beaudry in 2005 and became a shareholder of the firm in 2011. In 2013, he was awarded the "Relève d'excellence, consulting services" prize by the HEC Montréal network for emerging leaders.

-

Oeuvrant dans le domaine des ressources humaines depuis plus de 20 ans, Etienne a accompagné plusieurs organisations dans des projets visant l'optimisation de leur infrastructure de rémunération et mené des équipes de travail sur des projets complexes auprès d'un grand nombre d'organisations et de groupes sectoriels. Détenteur d’une maîtrise en gestion des ressources humaines de HEC Montréal, d’une maîtrise en gestion de la formation de l’Université de Sherbrooke et d’un programme exécutif en Intelligence Artificielle du MIT Sloan of Management, il a joint Normandin Beaudry en 2005 et est devenu actionnaire de la firme en 2011. En 2013, il s’est vu décerner le prix « Relève d’excellence, service de consultation », par le réseau de la relève de HEC Montréal.

biography: As a data scientist at La Presse, I apply my machine learning and NLP skills to analyze large-scale data and generate insights that inform the editorial and business decisions of the leading French-language digital news media in Canada. I have a master's degree in computer science from Université Laval, with a focus on artificial intelligence, and a master of science degree in information systems from Université Hassan II Mohammedia. I have over 7 years of professional experience in data science, having previously worked at PLANIFIKA, a consulting firm that specializes in asset management and optimization. There, I developed and deployed data-driven solutions for various clients in the public and private sectors, such as predictive models, dashboards, and reports. I also have experience as a teaching assistant at Université Laval, where I helped students learn the fundamentals of programming and algorithms. I am passionate about finding innovative ways to leverage data and technology to solve complex problems and create value for society. I am always eager to learn new skills, tools, and methods to improve my data science practice and stay updated on the latest trends and developments in the field. I value collaboration, curiosity, and creativity, and I strive to deliver high-quality results that meet the needs and expectations of my stakeholders.

biography:
Project manager with a strong interdisciplinary background, Vanessa has more than ten years of professional experience in various industries: science and technology museums, education and science vulgarization, organizational change, asset management and innovation consultant for international manufacturing companies. She is also an entrepreneurial artist with more than 18 professional exhibitions. Vanessa has an atypical background that makes her highly adaptable and professionally versatile.

Trained as a scientific museologist, Vanessa also holds doctoral schooling in applied human sciences, more precisely on ethical issues of natural science museum exhibitions. In 2020, she completed her academic career with an MBA at HEC Montréal which consolidates her business skills and confirms her interest in the effervescent space of new technologies, artificial intelligence and big data.

HINT 
Smarter, Faster, Impactful Content.
Et si nous combinions votre mémoire d'entreprise, en tenant compte de votre contexte actuel et de vos objectifs stratégiques, dans un aviseur intelligent?
Qui vous supporte en temps réel, pendant vos processus de création de contenu.
Et plus encore...
Intelligence d'affaires, Recherche scientifique et médicale, Communication interne et transfert de connaissances, Intégration de talents, Expertise en conseil, Formations décentralisées, etc.

HINT c'est :

Une efficacité optimisée : HINT génère un gain de productivité et un potentiel de revenus accru.
des Collaborations enrichies : HINT relie les individus et leurs idées, encourageant et facilitant la collaboration au sein des équipes.
des Résultats qualitatifs : HINT aide les équipes à rester alignées tout en explorant de nouvelles avenues, tout en respectant vos lignes éditoriales et vos objectifs stratégiques.

Fort de plus de 20 ans d’expérience en management, j’ai piloté des projets stratégiques qui transforment la donnée en levier de performance et de responsabilité environnementale.
Au Forum IA, je partagerai une vision pragmatique : comment l’IA peut accélérer la digitalisation, optimiser les opérations et soutenir la transition durable. Rejoignez-moi pour explorer ensemble des synergies entre technologie, industrie et durabilité.

biography:
Guillaume est co-fondateur, chef de la direction et président du Conseil d'administration de FX Innovation, une entreprise spécialisée dans la transformation numérique, et positionnée parmi les plus importantes PME québécoises et canadiennes.



Entrepreneur visionnaire et passionné, il s'intéresse particulièrement à la compréhension du cycle d'adoption des nouvelles technologies dans les différentes industries et déploie son énergie à développer avec ses équipes une vision claire, mobilisante et ambitieuse pour son organisation.



D'autres part, il est important pour Guillaume de prendre part à l'écosystème entrepreneurial ainsi qu'à celui de l'innovation québécois et canadien, notamment par son implication au sein du Canadian Council of Innovators ainsi qu'au Centre de Recherche Informatique de Montréal (CRIM) à titre de président du Conseil d'administration.




Guillaume is co-founder, CEO and Chairman of the Board of FX Innovation, a company specialized in digital transformation and positioned among the most important SMEs in Quebec and Canada.



A visionary and passionate entrepreneur, he is particularly interested in understanding the adoption cycle of new technologies in different industries and deploys his energy to develop with his teams a clear, mobilizing and ambitious vision for his organization.



It is also important for Guillaume to take part in the entrepreneurial ecosystem as well as in the Quebec and Canadian innovation ecosystem, notably through his involvement with the Canadian Council of Innovators and the Centre de Recherche Informatique de Montréal (CRIM) as Chairman of the Board.

biography:
I am a Toronto-based business journalist with The Canadian Press covering tech, cannabis and banks. I’ve previously worked at the Toronto Star and Globe and Mail. I've also appeared in the New York Times, the Guardian, Star Metro News and Maclean's. I’ve covered everything from business (tech, retail, real estate and food) to city news, entertainment, sports and life.

Have a pitch?
tsd@cp.org

Né à Evian-les-Bains en 1999, je suis aujourd'hui basé à Metz. 
Je découvre la réalité augmentée en 2017 grâce à Snapchat. De façon autodidacte et en dehors de mes études de journalisme, je me forme et comprends rapidement le potentiel de cette nouvelle technologie.
Depuis août 2021, je me suis professionnalisé avec la création de mon autoentreprise afin de travailler à temps complet sur des campagnes de communications ou des expériences en réalité augmentée au sens large. Je m’adresse à un panel de client aussi vaste que les idées de projet qu’il est possible de réaliser.
Je suis officiellement certifié par Meta en tant que créateur d'expérience AR pour Instagram/Facebook.

biography:
Daniel Giroux est le président et fondateur de la firme Axial Développement dont les bureaux sont situés à Sherbrooke, Gatineau et Québec, en plus d’offrir une grande présence à Montréal.
Depuis maintenant 10 ans Daniel s’investit auprès des clients avec qui il travaille en leur offrant son expertise qui allie technologie,  marketing et communication.  Il sait analyser en profondeur les besoins des clients pour leur offrir des solutions optimales adaptées.
Ses aptitudes de leader et de visionnaire lui permettent d’accomplir avec succès ses tâches de président d’entreprise.  Dynamique, enthousiaste, rigoureux et cultivé, Daniel cherche constamment à innover ses pratiques de dirigeant.  Il est toujours à l’affût d’idées créatrices pour son entreprise, mais aussi pour ses clients. Il est en quête constante du dépassement de soi, autant personnel que professionnel.
Il a récemment lancé avec fierté ekomobi.com, la toute nouvelle plate-forme de création de sites Web adaptés pour mobiles pensée, créée et réalisée par Axial Développement. C’est dans cette attitude de dépassement constante qu’il progresse et chemine pour sa propre entreprise mais aussi, et toujours, pour ses clients actuels et futurs!

Specialties: Développement de site Web, Web Mobile et d'application Web avec auto-gestion du contenu.

biography:
Mike is the VP, Growth & Strategy, Data & AI at Moov AI and formerly Canada Chief Data Scientist for Accenture Canada. Mike is passionate about leveraging data, analytics, and AI to propel organizations' competitive advantage, drawing on his unique experience in data science, machine learning, cloud architecture, data monetization, economics, leadership, and strategic advisory.

His philosophy is based on three fundamental pillars: Empowering teams to foster a creative and high-performing environment; Creating go-to-market plans focused on tangible results for clients and stakeholders; Commitment to responsible applications that prioritize ethics, privacy, and security

Convinced that enlightened leadership enables organizations to unlock their full potential and make a significant impact, he is dedicated to driving transformative change


---


Mike est le Directeur général chez Moov AI et anciennement Scientifique en chef des données pour Accenture Canada. Mike est passionné par l'utilisation des données, de l'analytique et de l'IA pour propulser l'avantage concurrentiel des organisations, s'appuyant sur son expérience unique en science des données, apprentissage automatique, architecture cloud, monétisation des données, économie, leadership et conseil stratégique.

Sa philosophie repose sur trois piliers fondamentaux : Autonomiser les équipes pour favoriser un environnement créatif et performant ; Élaborer des plans de mise sur le marché axés sur des résultats tangibles pour les clients et les parties prenantes ; S'engager dans des applications responsables qui priorisent l'éthique, la confidentialité et la sécurité.

Convaincu qu'un leadership éclairé permet aux organisations de libérer leur plein potentiel et d'avoir un impact significatif, il se consacre à conduire des changements transformateurs

biography:
I founded Foci Solutions to help software companies build better and faster engineering teams. I am passionate about instilling a culture of learning and curiosity in teams and believe that is the key to unlocking future potential. I believe that the strongest companies are those who optimize for future potential rather than point-in-time productivity.

I am a technology realist that believes in the potential and power of AI, but also recognize the need to adopt it responsibly and sustainably. I love working on real-world enterprise scale applications of AI beyond just chatbots and co-pilots.

At Foci Solutions, we help large enterprise and public sector clients automate and transform their most critical business processes and services through the adoption of modern technology such as Cloud and AI. We have worked with customers all over the globe and across a broad range of sectors ranging from biotechnology to cybersecurity.

But we don't just build apps or technology solutions. We also help our clients build teams and capacity. We believe that technology is only valuable is our clients can sustain them without us. We partner with our clients to ensure they have the necessary skills and resources to continue to sustain and evolve our solutions long after the project is done.

biography: Dr. Ahmed Ragab is a Lead Scientist in AI at Natural Resources Canada (NRCan). He is also an Adjunct Professor at the Department of Mathematics and Industrial Engineering, Polytechnique Montréal. He received a Ph.D. degree in Industrial Engineering from Polytechnique Montréal, the University of Montréal, Canada in 2014. Dr. Ragab’s research interests include AI, Machine Learning, Pattern Recognition, Image Processing, Data & Decisions Fusion, Causality Analysis, Reliability Modeling, Operations Research, Discrete Event Systems, and Process Mining. His main thematic activities focus on the practical challenges of Big Data and AI in several industrial applications including Abnormal Events Diagnosis & Prognosis, Predictive Maintenance, Supervisory Control, Real-time Optimization, Production Scheduling, and Systems Design. Dr. Ragab has a bunch of experience in developing advanced AI algorithms and tools in the manufacturing industry, aiming at reducing energy consumption, Greenhouse gas (GHG) emissions, and operational and maintenance costs while improving operations’ performance. He also teaches industrial engineering courses at graduate levels and supervises MSc and PhD students.

biography: Co-fondateur de volenretard.ca et de flightclaim.ca en 2016, Jacob Charbonneau fut auparavant responsable de l’optimisation de la performance et de la qualité pour le plus important transporteur aérien canadien spécialisé dans les voyages vacances. Il détient une maîtrise exécutive en administration des affaires, obtenue à l’université de Sherbrooke. Il est aussi impliqué au niveau de l’association des MBA du Québec et auprès de l’ordre des administrateurs agréés. M. Charbonneau a participé au changement législatif canadien pour la mise en place d’un régime de protection des voyageurs aériens. Il a été impliqué devant la Chambre des communes, le Sénat et l’office de transport du Canada en tant qu’expert.

biography:
Louis-Philippe Desjardins est directeur principal en cybersécurité chez Deloitte Canada et détient un baccalauréat en ingénierie de l’École Polytechnique de Montréal ainsi qu’un MBA de l’Université de Sherbrooke.
Il possède plus de 10 années d’expérience en cybersécurité, autant comme gestionnaire dans de grandes entreprises industrielles qu’en consultation.
Son expertise technique d’ingénieur logiciel combinée à sa compréhension des enjeux liés aux affaires sont des atouts essentiels qui lui permettent de comprendre les véritables problèmes des entreprises, d’aider les dirigeants à définir leurs besoins, d’apprécier les contraintes techniques, d’identifier les solutions possibles et de créer de la valeur pour les organisations. 
Au fil des années, il a aidé plusieurs entreprises évoluant dans différents secteurs à développer et implanter des stratégies afin de gérer efficacement les risques liés à la cybersécurité.

biography:
I’m a serial entrepreneur based in Canada. My goal : create wealth for my community and work for a sustainable and socially responsible world. 

I joined CONFORMiT in September 2015 as owner, President & Chief Executive Officer. CONFORMiT is a leading global Environmental, Health & Safety Management (EHS) SaaS solution. With clients in 20 countries with more than 700,000 users, CONFORMiT is one of the international leaders that offers a complete set of solutions to help organizations better manage their EHS processes - in the simplest way.

From 2010 to August 2015, I was in charge of the development (Sales & Delivery) in Central of Europe and Nordic countries with PCO Innovation (now Accenture). In 2002, I founded a company that offers strategic consulting services in information technology. Under my leadership, the company experienced strong growth and became a key player in the Canadian market. I launched five other successful companies in the fields of technology, internet services, consulting and food service. I also held the position of vice-president of outsourcing and telecommunication at Cognicase, a company with $400 million in sales, Cognicase was acquired by CGI in 2003. I was in the Canadian Armed Forces for seven years.

biography:
Engineer, passionate about innovation and intellectual property (IP) strategy. 

My work has been focused on intellectual property for nearly 30 years. I am passionate about innovation and about supporting clients on IP matters throughout their journey.  I am familiar with all aspects of patent procurement in Canada and the United States, including: preparing and prosecuting applications; managing IP portfolios; conducting freedom-to-operate assessments; and developing strategies that support the business objectives of clients. I provide counselling and support during IP due diligence during transactions.  I also work with litigation teams by offering expertise in the preparation of patent infringement and validity opinions. My particular technical expertise lies in the areas of electronics, telecommunications, business methods, control systems, medical devices, machine learning, Artificial Intelligence, software and related technologies. 

I am passionate about about increasing awareness of the strategic importance of intellectual property rights in the local business community and in particular for small and medium sized companies (SMEs).

biography:
Ingénieure bilingue cumulant plus de 25 années d’expérience en gestion, je me distingue par mon leadership, mes habiletés relationnelles, mon sens des affaires, ma capacité à rallier une équipe autour d’une même vision et à opérationnaliser un changement stratégique pour une organisation. J’ai surtout œuvré dans les secteurs bancaire et de la santé et, en particulier, au sein d’importants projets de modernisation et de transformation.

Mon expertise se situe principalement en gestion de projets de transformation, en gestion et optimisation des opérations et en intégration des technologies numériques. J’accorde une grande importance aux processus d’affaire, à la performance et à l’implication des différents intervenants.  Depuis quelques mois, j'occupe le poste de leader de l'efficience organisationnelle.   J'appuie les membres du comité de direction et leurs équipes dans la réussite de notre transformation et dans la réalisation des bénéfices ciblés par nos projets technologiques.

biography:
Julien specializes in advising companies on intellectual property matters relating to software, with a particular interest in artificial intelligence and other emerging technologies. He is a professional engineer who completed is Master of Advanced Studies in data mining at GERAD, a multi university research center regrouping experts from HEC Montréal, Polytechnique Montréal, McGill University and Université du Québec à Montréal. He is also a registered patent agent in Canada and the United States.

Julien has extensive experience in the building of patent portfolios for companies of various sizes, from start-up ventures looking to increase their value and attract funding, to multinational organizations preparing to enter new markets. Julien has particular experience drafting and prosecuting patent applications in the United States, Canada, Europe and China, advising on patent infringement and avoidance issues, and shaping and implementing comprehensive intellectual property strategies supporting business objectives and corporate strategies.

Julien is a member of the Organizing Committee of “Le Forum international de la propriété intellectuelle — Québec (FORPIQ)”, a non-profit organization devoted to increasing the level of knowledge of innovative Canadian companies and their advisers about intellectual property assets. 

Julien also guest-lectures on design patents and animates a workshop on patent filing strategy and a workshop on advanced claim drafting for the IPIC program at McGill University.

biography:
I am a computer science graduate student with a strong interdisciplinary background in applying computer science to biological and ecological problems. I applied my skills in many research projects, such as developing data pipelines for predictive models for biodiversity in a post-climate change world and classifying budding yeast dynamics using machine learning. I use Python Tensorflow and R the most but I have experience using a wide variety of languages and tools.

I have an interest in healthcare and climate change challenges through computational solutions, but I am always excited to learn something new. I also have a track record of taking on leadership roles from leading a hackathon team to teaching programming to large student groups.
